A new book on former Pres­ident Olusegun Obasanjo would be launched on Mon­day, December 28 in Lagos. The book titled: “The man, The General, The President”, written by a former aide of Obasanjo during his second term as president, Otunba Femmy Carrena, was de­scribed as an eyewitness account of the seeming un­known sides of the former president. According to the author and the Obasanjo Presidential Library, who are organisers of the event, the founder and Chairman of Channels Tele­vision, Mr. John Momoh, will be the chairman of the event while business mogul, Chief Kessington Adebutu (CON) is the Chief Launcher. Gov­ernors Babajide Sanwo-Olu and Dapo Abiodun of Lagos and Ogun states are expected as Special Guests of honour at the event. Also expected is the Founder and Chairman of Zenith Bank, Mr. Jim Ovia, among other dignitaries in­vited to the event, which will start by 11.am. SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION